narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I was given valuable feedback for my presentation this semester. Josephina also spent a lot of time curating my classmates' feedback into an easily digestible format for me after the presentation. I appreciate the time and hard work she put in this class.
How to critically evaluate scientific presentations

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Stop making everything mandatory. It really takes away from the point of this course.

The introductory class (the first class of the semester) was a bit too long and drawn out. The wealth of information clearly came from a place of caring, however, as Josephina and David clearly wanted to make sure we were all aware of proper presentation etiquette. I appreciate that
Weakness - It would be helpful if the link for the feedback survey was provided at least once through email at the beginning of the semester

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes, Josephina was very engaged and put a lot of time and effort into the class and giving us all valuable feedback.
